  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Main Con)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Conduct estimations for variation submissions and manage price comparisons to ensure accurate project costing.</li>\n  <li>Prepare progress claims, evaluate supplier payments, and handle variation orders, finalizing accounts accordingly.</li>\n  <li>Perform quantity measurements, monitor project variations, and attend site and consultant meetings for updates and discussions.</li>\n  <li>Support ad-hoc tasks and duties assigned by supervisors and management, ensuring timely and efficient completion.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Quantity Surveying or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 4 years of experience as a Quantity Surveyor in <strong>Construction industry (Main Con).</strong></li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office applications - Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
